You're only exposing:





emulator console (5554)



noVNC (6080)

You're not exposing the ADB port (5555).

The working docker run publishes three ports:

5554  emulator console
5555  adb
6080  noVNC


Fix

Your method should create three exposed ports.

ExposedPort console = ExposedPort.tcp(5554);
ExposedPort adb = ExposedPort.tcp(5555);
ExposedPort webVnc = ExposedPort.tcp(6080);


Then

Ports bindings = new Ports();

bindings.bind(console,
        Ports.Binding.bindPort(consolePort));

bindings.bind(adb,
        Ports.Binding.bindPort(adbPort));

bindings.bind(webVnc,
        Ports.Binding.bindPort(vncPort));


and

.withExposedPorts(console, adb, webVnc)


Why this matters

The image internally does something like

emulator
        │
        ▼
5554  emulator console

5555  adb daemon


Publishing only 5554 is not equivalent to publishing both 5554 and 5555.

Your manual docker run exposed both, and that's the one that booted successfully.

